abstract: Mo Farah wins two-mile race at Birmingham Grand Prix in record 8 minutes 3.40 seconds.
lead_paragraph: The two-time Olympic champion Mo Farah ran the fastest-ever indoor time over two miles at the Birmingham Grand Prix in England, finishing in 8 minutes 3.40 seconds in his first race of 2015.

headline.main: Mo Farah Breaks Indoor Two-Mile Record
